# Copy this file to `.sandcastle/.env` and fill in a value.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub Copilot CLI authentication
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The agent runs the GitHub Copilot CLI, which authenticates with a GitHub token
# whose account has an ACTIVE GitHub Copilot subscription (Individual, Business,
# or Enterprise). A token alone is not enough — the account must have a Copilot seat.
#
# COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN takes precedence over GH_TOKEN and GITHUB_TOKEN; set
# whichever one you prefer — just one is required.
#
# ── Quickest option: the GitHub CLI mints a token for you ────────────────────
#   gh auth login
#   gh auth token        # prints a token you can paste below
#
# ── Create a fine-grained Personal Access Token via the GitHub website ───────
#   1. Sign in at https://github.com.
#   2. Top-right profile photo → Settings.
#   3. Left sidebar, scroll to the bottom → Developer settings.
#   4. Personal access tokens → Fine-grained tokens.
#   5. Click "Generate new token".
#   6. Fill in:
#        - Token name:     e.g. sandcastle-copilot
#        - Expiration:     pick a duration (e.g. 90 days)
#        - Resource owner: your account (or the org that holds the Copilot seat)
#   7. Under Permissions → Account permissions, find "Copilot Requests"
#      (shown as GitHub Copilot Chat/Requests) and set it to Read-only.
#      No repository permissions are needed for the CLI to authenticate.
#   8. Click "Generate token".
#   9. Copy the token immediately (it is shown only once) and paste it below.
#      Fine-grained tokens look like:  github_pat_xxxxxxxx
#
#   Direct link to the creation page:
#      https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
#
# ── Alternative: classic token ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic) →
#   Generate new token (classic). Classic tokens have no granular Copilot
#   checkbox; they work as long as the account has a Copilot seat. Give it a
#   minimal scope such as read:user, then paste it as GH_TOKEN below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Alternatively (only one token is needed):
# GH_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Agent backend and model selection
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SANDCASTLE_AGENT selects the agent backend. Supported values: copilot (default), claude.
#
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL sets the default model for all steps.
# Each step can be overridden individually with SANDCASTLE_MODEL_<STEP>.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SANDCASTLE_AGENT=copilot
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4.6

# Per-step model overrides (fall back to SANDCASTLE_MODEL if not set):
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_REFINE=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_TECHNICAL=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_PLAN=claude-opus-4.8
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_TESTS=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_IMPLEMENT=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_ACCEPTANCE=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_REVIEW=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_COMMIT=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_IMPROVE=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_IMPROVE-SELF=
# SANDCASTLE_MODEL_SUMMARIZE=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sandbox image and local paths
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SANDCASTLE_IMAGE overrides the Podman image name/tag built from
# .sandcastle/Containerfile (default: sandcastle:userstory-pipeline).
#
# SANDCASTLE_WORK_DIR overrides where target repositories are cloned on the
# host (default: .work inside this repo). Use this to clone onto a different
# disk/drive or a shared cache location.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SANDCASTLE_IMAGE=sandcastle:userstory-pipeline
# SANDCASTLE_WORK_DIR=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Loop caps, iterations & timeouts
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SANDCASTLE_MAX_AC:        acceptance-criteria loop cap before human escalation (default 5)
# SANDCASTLE_MAX_REVIEW:    code-review loop cap before human escalation (default 5)
# SANDCASTLE_MAX_IMPLEMENT: safety cap on the implement→test loop (default 10)
# SANDCASTLE_IMPLEMENT_ITERATIONS: agent iterations per implement invocation (default 1)
# SANDCASTLE_IDLE_TIMEOUT:  per-step agent idle timeout in seconds (default 1200)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SANDCASTLE_MAX_AC=5
# SANDCASTLE_MAX_REVIEW=5
# SANDCASTLE_MAX_IMPLEMENT=10
# SANDCASTLE_IMPLEMENT_ITERATIONS=1
# SANDCASTLE_IDLE_TIMEOUT=1200

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Story inputs (optional convenience — normally passed as CLI flags)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any input not supplied via --title/--description/--repo/--base-branch and
# not set here is prompted for interactively.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SANDCASTLE_TITLE=
# SANDCASTLE_DESCRIPTION=
# SANDCASTLE_REPO=
# SANDCASTLE_BASE_BRANCH=main
